LSP support:

* bash:
  * Ubuntu: sudo snap install bash-language-server --classic
  * Fedora: dnf install -y nodejs-bash-language-server
* C
  * Ubuntu: sudo apt install clangd
  * Fedora: sudo dnf install clang-tools-extra
  * Read https://clangd.llvm.org/installation#project-setup
* Docker:
  * [sudo] npm install -g dockerfile-language-server-nodejs
* HTML/CSS/JSON/ESLint:
  * [sudo] npm i -g vscode-langservers-extracted
* Java: See file build-jdtls
* LaTeX:
  * Ubuntu: sudo apt-get install texlab
  * Others: cd ~/bin/Linux-x86_64 && wget https://github.com/latex-lsp/texlab/releases/download/v5.25.1/texlab-x86_64-linux.tar.gz && tar xzf texlab-x86_64-linux.tar.gz && rm -f texlab-x86_64-linux.tar.gz
* Markdown:
  * Ubuntu: sudo snap install marksman
  * Others: cd ~/bin/Linux-x86_64 && wget -O marksman https://github.com/artempyanykh/marksman/releases/download/2026-02-08/marksman-linux-x64 && chmod +x marksman
* Pyhon:
  * uv tool install pyright
* Rust:
  * May need to run "rustup update" first (or that may be sufficient!).
    cargo install ra_ap_rust-analyzer
* YAML:
  * Ubuntu: [sudo] snap install yaml-language-server



